tickerNews.title: BBRI: February-25 Performance Recovered, CEO Changed, and Final Dividend Rp208/Share
tickerNews.content:
The Annual General Meeting of Shareholders (AGMS) of Bank Rakyat Indonesia (BBRI) on Monday (24/3) approved the proposal for changes in the board of directors and commissioners, with Hery Gunardi becoming the President Director of BBRI, replacing Sunarso who had served since 2019. Hery previously served as the President Director of Bank Syariah Indonesia (BRIS).
Furthermore, BBRI shareholders also approved the distribution of the 2024 fiscal year dividend amounting to approximately 52 trillion rupiah, equivalent to an 86% dividend payout ratio (vs. 2023: 80%). This amount indicates a final dividend of 208.4 rupiah per share and a yield of 5.8%, based on BBRI's closing share price on Monday (24/3) at 3,610 rupiah per share. Previously, BBRI had distributed an interim dividend for the 2024 fiscal year of 135 rupiah per share in January 2025.
Last weekend, BBRI announced (https://www.ir-bri.com/misc/QR/2025/BRI_Lapkeu_M02_2025_Eng.pdf) a net profit (bank only) of 4.6 trillion rupiah in February 2025 (+42% YoY, +129% MoM), a significant recovery from the low performance in January 2025. This result brought the bank only net profit for 2M25 to 6.6 trillion rupiah (-18% YoY), below the consensus consolidated growth estimate for 2025F at -1.3% YoY following the effect of management overlay (https://stockbit.com/post/17707020) in January 2025.
The normalization of credit cost (CoC) became the main driver for the recovery of bank only net profit in February 2025, in line with the management guidance (https://stockbit.com/post/17714295) provided after the release of bank only performance for January 2025. Besides CoC normalization, the recovery of Net Interest Margin (NIM) was also a positive aspect we highlighted. Meanwhile, the surge in opex became a concern for us.
- CoC Normalized after Surge in January 2025: BBRI recorded a bank only CoC at the level of 3.28% in February 2025 (vs. January 2025: 5.57%, February 2024: 6.72%) following provisioning expenses which began to normalize to 3.3 trillion rupiah (-49% YoY, -41% MoM). This result brought the CoC for 2M25 to 4.42% (vs. 2M24: 4.38%), still above management's consolidated FY25 guidance which targets a range of 3-3.2%. The normalization of CoC is a good early indication that front-loading provisions have been overcome. Asset quality developments will remain our focus, including in the 1Q25 earnings call discussion.
- NIM Recovered: Bank only NIM increased to 6.39% in February 2025 (vs. February 2024: 6.17%, January 2025: 6.15%) following relatively good Net Interest Income (NII) realization at 9.3 trillion rupiah (+3% YoY, +4.7% MoM). This good NII was also driven by a significant drop in interest expense to 3.9 trillion rupiah (-8.7% YoY, -4.8% MoM) along with a decrease in time deposits of -9.8% YoY. For 2M25, NIM was at 6.25% (vs. 2M24: 6.4%), still below management's consolidated FY25 guidance targeting a range of 7.3-7.7%. In the January 2025 performance earnings call, BBRI management expected loan growth and liquidity conditions to start improving in 2Q25, which could positively impact NIM.
- Opex Surge: Opex increased to 4.3 trillion rupiah (+111% YoY, -9.6% MoM) in February 2025, causing 2M25 opex to surge to 9.1 trillion rupiah (+37% YoY). This opex surge was mainly driven by an increase in labor costs to 4.2 trillion rupiah during 2M25 (+20% YoY). This cost increase was primarily due to the difference in timing related to the booking of holiday allowance (THR) expenses. A more apple-to-apple opex comparison compared to last year will be visible in the performance realization during 1Q25.

tickerNews.title: TPIA entered SSIA's Shareholders List
tickerNews.content: SSIA: Chandra Asri Pacific (TPIA) entered as a shareholder with ownership exceeding 5% in Surya Semesta Internusa, holding 250.6 million (5.33%) shares through Individual Customer Fund Management managed by Henan Putihrai Asset Management (PDNI HPAM - CAP Fund). This transaction was only recorded in the KSEI data (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/9ffde78a02_5b195f17b2.pdf) as of March 20, 2025, so the transaction value is unknown. Previously, TPIA was not included in the list of shareholders with ownership exceeding 5% in SSIA.

tickerNews.title: INTP: Recorded Net Profit of 952 Billion Rupiah in 4Q24
tickerNews.content: INTP: Indocement Tunggal Prakarsa recorded (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202403/20250321194654-50527-0/LKFS%20ITP%2031Dec2024_INTP_210325.pdf) a net profit of 952 billion rupiah in 4Q24 (+39% YoY, +53% QoQ). This result brought the net profit for 2024 to 2 trillion rupiah (+3% YoY), exceeding consensus expectations (125% of the 2024F consensus estimate). The net profit growth in 4Q24 was supported by a rise in gross profit margin to 37.8% (+280 bps YoY, +350 bps QoQ) and an expansion of operating profit margin to 18.6% (+440 bps YoY, +330 bps QoQ), marking the highest levels since at least 3Q21 and 1Q21, respectively. Throughout 2024, the gross profit margin and operating profit margin increased slightly to 32.7% (vs. 2023: 32.6%) and 12.6% (vs. 2023: 12.4%), respectively. Previously (https://snips.stockbit.com/snips-terbaru/-bi-rate-turun-25-bps-di-luar-ekspektasi#:~:text=%24INTP%3A%C2%A0Indocement,tumbuh%20%2B1%2C1%25%20YoY.), INTP noted that cement sales volume (including Semen Grobogan) in 4Q24 grew +6% YoY, resulting in a +8.4% YoY increase in sales volume throughout 2024.

tickerNews.title: NISP: Bank OCBC NISP Plans to Distribute 2024 Fiscal Year Dividend
tickerNews.content: NISP: Bank OCBC NISP plans (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/fdecfa031a_23e5d68c83.pdf) to distribute the 2024 fiscal year dividend amounting to ~2.4 trillion rupiah or 106 rupiah per share, equivalent to a 50% dividend payout ratio. The cum date in the regular and negotiation market is April 8, 2025, with payment on April 17, 2025. Referring to NISP's share price at the market close on Monday (24/3) at 1,310 rupiah per share, the indicative dividend yield is 8.1%.

tickerNews.title: SCMA: Majority Controller Elang Mahkota Teknologi (EMTK) Bought Shares
tickerNews.content: SCMA: The controller of Surya Citra Media, Elang Mahkota Teknologi (EMTK), purchased ~220.7 million SCMA shares at a price of 200 rupiah per share on March 19-20, 2025. The total transaction value reached ~44 billion rupiah. After this transaction (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/c43af746a9_ce2a9e01d7.pdf), EMTK's ownership in SCMA increased from 63.33% to 63.63%.

tickerNews.title: HEAL: Medikaloka Hermina Plans Share Buyback Up to 95 Million Shares
tickerNews.content: HEAL: Medikaloka Hermina plans a share buyback of up to 95 million shares with a maximum fund allocation of 100 billion rupiah from March 21 to May 2, 2025. The company limits the maximum buyback price to 1,680 rupiah per share. This corporate action (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/285b46a1f6_286145ddce.pdf) does not require an AGMS, in line with the relaxation provided by the OJK to support capital market stability.

tickerNews.title: SMGR: Semen Indonesia Recorded Cement Sales Volume of 3 Million Tons in February 2025
tickerNews.content: SMGR: Semen Indonesia recorded a cement sales volume of 3 million tons in February 2025 (+5% YoY, +3% MoM). This result brought SMGR's cement sales volume for 2M25 to 6 million tons (-1.3% YoY). The cement sales volume growth in February 2025 was supported by an increase in sales from Indonesian facilities to 2.9 million tons (+4.5% YoY, +2.7% MoM). In terms of product segmentation, bag cement sales contributed 72% of total sales in February 2025 (vs. January 2025: 72.5%) and 72.3% during 2M25.

tickerNews.title: ERAL: Sinar Eka Selaras Recorded Net Profit of 44 Billion Rupiah in 4Q24
tickerNews.content: ERAL: Sinar Eka Selaras recorded (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202403/20250321164917-50250-0/ERAL%20-%20Laporan%20Keuangan%20(Audited)%202024.pdf) a net profit of 44 billion rupiah in 4Q24 (-6% YoY, -35% QoQ). This result brought the net profit for 2024 to 201 billion rupiah (-4.4% YoY). Revenue in 4Q24 grew to 1.4 trillion rupiah (+36% YoY, +7.1% QoQ), making the revenue for 2024 reach 4.8 trillion rupiah (+30% YoY). Weak operating profit in 4Q24 (-1.7% YoY, -30% QoQ) was caused by a surge in opex-to-sales ratio to 11% (vs. 4Q23: 9.6%, 3Q24: 9.2%), causing the operating profit margin to drop to 3.8% (vs. 4Q23: 5.2%, 3Q24: 5.8%).

tickerNews.title: WINS: Wintermar Offshore Marine Recorded Net Profit of US$2.8 Million in 4Q24
tickerNews.content: WINS: Wintermar Offshore Marine recorded (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202403/20250324101237-50460-0/Wins_LK_31Des2024.pdf) a net profit of US$2.8 million in 4Q24 (-56% QoQ, -28% YoY). This result brought the net profit for 2024 to US$22.5 million (+237% YoY), below our expectation (80.5% of Stockbit's 2024F estimate). Quarterly, the decline in net profit was caused by a revenue decrease (-10.1% QoQ) and a reversal of other income to a loss of US$0.1 million (vs. 3Q24: profit of US$1.7 million).

tickerNews.title: Government Transfers Ownership of Several SOEs to BPI Danantara
tickerNews.content:
The Indonesian Government began transferring ownership of a number of State-Owned Enterprises (SOEs) to BPI Danantara, based on information disclosure on Monday (24/3). A number of these SOEs include Bank Rakyat Indonesia (BBRI) (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/77bfddf3ac_531ae507f8.pdf), Bank Mandiri (BMRI) (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/84f51de2b3_20b609f116.pdf), Bank Negara Indonesia (BBNI) (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/381864622e_02fd3f326f.pdf), Bank Tabungan Negara (BBTN) (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/736eb60778_eb73006132.pdf), Telkom Indonesia (TLKM) (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/46b55b5b3b_d6468a2f39.pdf), Semen Indonesia (SMGR) (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/dd7c24b810_18eb084c15.pdf), Jasa Marga (JSMR) (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/9e11219d5f_754a4a9e15.pdf), Waskita Karya (WSKT) (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/b531efa523_e530d47c8b.pdf), Wijaya Karya (WIKA) (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/70d0f0cedf_b7ebdd4cd0.pdf), Adhi Karya (ADHI) (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/7bb6071cd6_cc2bbaa9ca.pdf), PP (PTPP) (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/dad29958e5_55d0e396fc.pdf), Garuda Indonesia (GIAA) (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/3ccc3e54f8_fbab039ad0.pdf), and Krakatau Steel (KRAS) (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/0c226fddd3_28bec7bd57.pdf). Nevertheless, the strongest share series in these SOEs - i.e., Series A shares - remain under government control.
On Monday (24/3), the CEO of BPI Danantara, Rosan Roeslani, announced (https://market.bisnis.com/read/20250324/192/1864200/struktur-lengkap-organisasi-dan-pengurus-danantara-indonesia) the organizational structure along with the complete list of Danantara officials. The complete list of advisors consists of Ray Dalio, Helman Sitohang, Jeffrey Sachs, F. Chapman Taylor, and Thaksin Shinawatra. In addition to the supervisory board, Danantara has an oversight committee, a risk management committee, and an investment and portfolio committee.

tickerNews.title: GOTO to Distribute Holiday Bonuses to Driver Partners
tickerNews.content: Chief of Public Policy & Government Relations GoTo Gojek Tokopedia (GOTO), Ade Mulya, said (https://money.kompas.com/read/2025/03/23/141000626/goto-bagikan-bonus-hari-raya-ke-mitra-pengemudi-gojek-ini-kategori-dan#google_vignette) that the company began distributing holiday bonuses (BHR) for driver partners. Ade explained that BHR is not a holiday allowance (THR) like that received by official workers, but rather a directive from President Prabowo Subianto and adjusted to the company's financial capacity to remain sustainable. GOTO divides BHR recipients into 5 categories based on partner performance: 50,000 rupiah, 100,000 rupiah, 500,000 rupiah, 800,000 rupiah, and 1.6 million rupiah.

tickerNews.title: PNBN Plans Share Buyback Allocating Maximum Funds of 500 Billion Rupiah
tickerNews.content: Bank Pan Indonesia (PNBN) plans a share buyback of approximately 286-416 million shares with a maximum fund allocation of 500 billion rupiah from March 24 to June 23, 2025. The company will conduct the buyback in the price range of 1,200-1,750 rupiah per share. This corporate action (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/53074170b5_2cd2a0f8bb.pdf) does not require an AGMS, in line with the relaxation provided by the OJK to support capital market stability.

tickerNews.title: Indonesia's February Refined Tin Exports Reached 3,926.93 Metric Tons
tickerNews.content: The Ministry of Trade recorded (https://www.tradingview.com/news/reuters.com,2025:newsml_L3N3Q7096:0-indonesia-s-february-refined-tin-exports-at-3-926-93-metric-tons-trade-ministry-says/) that Indonesia's refined tin exports reached 3,926.93 tons in February 2025 (+150% MoM), soaring +7,040% YoY from a realization of 55 tons in February 2024 when shipments were disrupted by mining permit delays.

tickerNews.title: SAME: Majority Controller Elang Mahkota Teknologi (EMTK) Bought Shares
tickerNews.content: The controller of Sarana Meditama Metropolitan (SAME), Elang Mahkota Teknologi (EMTK), purchased 100 million SAME shares at a price of 320 rupiah per share on March 20, 2025. The total transaction value reached 32 billion rupiah. After this transaction (https://www.idx.co.id/StaticData/NewsAndAnnouncement/ANNOUNCEMENTSTOCK/From_EREP/202503/0a1c136105_ae8f12c794.pdf), EMTK's ownership in SAME increased from 78.46% to 79.04%.

tickerNews.title: TMAS: Shareholders Approved 2024 Fiscal Year Dividend Distribution
tickerNews.content: Temas (TMAS) shareholders approved (https://market.bisnis.com/read/20250324/192/1864078/emiten-pelayaran-temas-tmas-akan-tebar-dividen-rp2282-miliar) the plan to distribute the 2024 fiscal year dividend amounting to 228.2 billion rupiah or 4 rupiah per share, equivalent to a 34% dividend payout ratio. The cum date and payment date have not yet been announced. Referring to TMAS's share price at the close on Monday (24/3) at 126 rupiah per share, the indicative dividend yield is 3.2%.
